{"type":"message","id":"925ee9a3","parentId":"37129b9b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:52.627Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m9yd61yoiyie_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5149\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3332\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master c0301be] pulse: 2026-03-23 194521\n 7 files changed, 362 insertions(+), 119 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 194521.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 194521.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 192348.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 194521 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: if causal structure IS invariant structure, we can test this by building a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on existing pulse logs.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidal-bloom","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5149\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3332\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] a\r\n[mutation proposed] a\r\n[master c0301be] pulse: 2026-03-23 194521\n 7 files changed, 362 insertions(+), 119 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 194521.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 194521.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 192348.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 194521 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a concrete path forward: if causal structure IS invariant structure, we can test this by building a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on existing pulse logs.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309552625}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e36d20b","parentId":"925ee9a3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:52.629Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_m9yd61yoiyie_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 192348\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine ONE concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (Architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Next action is the TIC Experiment - implementing TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n- Need to measure invariant/variant classification accuracy and predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to implement the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC classifier implementation\r\n3. Document the approach\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory and understand the pulse log format.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to take ONE concrete action. The best action is to implement the core of the TIC experiment. Let me create the TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\nLooking at the logs mentioned: `logs/pulse_*.md` files, with the most recent being `pulse_2026-03-23 191349.md`.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. The script should identify invariant (persistent) vs variant (changing) content across pulses\r\n3. Then use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nLet me create this implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step. It requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs, then uses invariants to predict next pulse content. This unifies Phase 1 (compression) and Phase 2 (causal discovery) into one problem.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_classifier.py` - the core TIC implementation that:\r\n1. Parses pulse log files\r\n2. Extracts features (goals, actions, outcomes, insights)\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant (persistent across pulses) or variant (changing)\r\n4. Predicts next pulse from invariant structure\r\n5. Outputs classification accuracy metrics\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n================================================\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Set, Tuple\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass PulseFeatures:\r\n    \"\"\"Extracted features from a single pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    timestamp: str\r\n    goals: Set[str]\r\n    actions: List[str]\r\n    outcomes: List[str]\r\n    insights: List[str]\r\n    pending: Set[str]\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_path: Path) -> PulseFeatures:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured features from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract timestamp from filename\r\n    match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d+)\\.md', pulse_path.name)\r\n    timestamp = f\"{match.group(1)} {match.group(2)}\" if match else \"unknown\"\r\n    \r\n    # Extract Goals section\r\n    goals = set()\r\n    goals_match = re.search(r'## Goals:.*?\\n(.*?)(?=\\n##|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if goals_match:\r\n        for line in goals_match.group(1).strip().split('\\n'):\r\n            line = line.strip()\r\n            if line and line.startswith('- '):\r\n                goals.add(line[2:].strip())\r\n            elif line.startswith('['):\r\n                goals.add(line)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract actions (lines starting with ### ACTION or bullet points)\r\n    actions = []\r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if '### ACTION' in line or line.strip().startswith('### MUTATION'):\r\n            actions.append(line.strip())\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insights (lines containing key insights, synthesis, hypothesis)\r\n    insights = []\r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if any(kw in line.lower() for kw in ['insight', 'synthesis', 'hypothesis', 'finding', 'key']):\r\n            insights.append(line.strip())\r\n    \r\n    # Extract pending items\r\n    pending = set()\r\n    pending_match = re.search(r'## Pending.*?\\n(.*?)(?=\\n##|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if pending_match:\r\n        for line in pending_match.group(1).strip().split('\\n'):\r\n            line = line.strip()\r\n            if line and (line.startswith('- [ ]') or line.startswith('- [')):\r\n                pending.add(line)\r\n    \r\n    return PulseFeatures(\r\n        timestamp=timestamp,\r\n        goals=goals,\r\n        actions=actions,\r\n        outcomes=[],  # Placeholder\r\n        insights=insights,\r\n        pending=pending\r\n    )\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_list: List[PulseFeatures]) -> Dict[str, str]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify features as INVARIANT (persistent across all pulses) \r\n    or VARIANT (changing between pulses).\r\n    \r\n    Returns dict mapping feature -> 'invariant' or 'variant'\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    classification = {}\r\n    \r\n    # Track feature occurrence across pulses\r\n    all_goals = set()\r\n    all_insights = set()\r\n    all_pending = set()\r\n    \r\n    for pf in features_list:\r\n        all_goals.update(pf.goals)\r\n        all_insights.update(pf.insights)\r\n        all_pending.update(pf.pending)\r\n    \r\n    # Count appearances of each goal\r\n    goal_counts = {}\r\n    for goal in all_goals:\r\n        count = sum(1 for pf in features_list if goal in pf.goals)\r\n        goal_counts[goal] = count\r\n    \r\n    # Goal appears in >70% of\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 19:24:14\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309552627}}
